INSAT-3DS Satellite

INSAT-3DS is an advanced meteorological satellite designed to provide continuity to the services of INSAT-3D, featuring identical sensors and products. It is a part of the INSAT (Indian National Satellite System), a series of multipurpose satellites launched by ISRO since 1983 to serve India's needs in telecommunications, broadcasting, meteorology, and search and rescue. The INSAT system is the largest domestic communication system in the Asia Pacific Region.

Mission and Launch
Mission Type: Multipurpose Geosynchronous Satellite

Launch Date: 2024-02-17

Launch Vehicle: GSLV-F14

Launch Site: Satish Dhawan Space Centre

Primary Objectives üõ∞Ô∏è
To provide an operational, environmental, and storm warning system to protect life and property.

